glosses: To be beaten up, to receive a beating, to get one's ass kicked.

examples.text: Küçükken çok dayak yedim, ama bu beni durdurmadı.
examples.translation: I got beaten up a lot when I was little, but that didn't stop me.

etymology: Inherited from Ottoman Turkish طیاق یمك (dayak yemek, “to receive a beating”), equivalent to compound of dayak (“beating, support”) + yemek (“to eat”), literally “to eat a beating”. Cognate with Kazakh таяқ жеу (taäq jeu).
